\end_inset

Was it rage that drove me? Is that what you think?
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Martin leaned his back against the invisible boundary of the containment
 cage.
 He couldn't stop looking at his shoes.
 Real leather, one of the last few pairs in existence.
 Made out of some kind of animal that had once lived.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

I can only assume Frank, but -
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

To merely assume it was blind rage would be an insult to her memory!
